  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the <strong>pizza bottom</strong> from going soggy!)</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-veggie-loaded-pizza-with-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-veggie-loaded-pizza-with-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain your<strong> mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-veggie-loaded-pizza-with-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>bbq sauce</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 5 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[7 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[10 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>bbq base</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-veggie-loaded-pizza-with-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>bbq base </strong>evenly over the pizza base[s] with the back of a spoon</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-veggie-loaded-pizza-with-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top with the <strong>pepper strips</strong>, <strong>sliced red onion</strong>, <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> and <strong>torn mozzarella</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the base[s] are crisp – this is your <strong>bbq veggie loaded pizza</strong></p><p>Tip: Make sure the pizza[s] don't overlap on the tray to avoid raw dough!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-veggie-loaded-pizza-with-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pizza[s] are nearly done, wash your <strong>salad </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to a large bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Toss it all together – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-veggie-loaded-pizza-with-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bbq veggie loaded pizza</strong> and top with the <strong>dressed salad</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
